The paper deals with the model checking problem for the existential fragment of first-order logic on partially ordered sets, which is a topic that falls under the scope of logic (cs.LO) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also involves algorithmic techniques and complexity analysis, which are relevant to computer science theory (cs.CC). Additionally, the study of partially ordered sets is closely related to the field of discrete structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper's focus on improving the runtime of an algorithm for model checking suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), where efficient algorithms are often crucial for solving complex problems.
